Yaya Toure has expressed remorse for the victims and their families of last week's Charlie Hebdo attacks in Paris.

Manchester City midfielder Toure, a practising Muslim, apologised on behalf of his religion and admitted he was 'afraid of what is going to happen.'

Twelve people were killed when two gunmen entered French satirical magazine Charlie Hebdo's offices in Paris.

